properties.headline: Wind Chill Advisory issued February 13 at 3:34PM EST until February 14 at 9:00AM EST by NWS Marquette MI
properties.description:
* WHAT...Cold wind chills expected. Wind chills 25 to 30 below
zero at times.

* WHERE...Gogebic, Iron and Dickinson Counties.

* WHEN...From 8 PM this evening to 8 AM CST Friday.

* IMPACTS...The cold wind chills could cause frostbite on exposed
skin in as little as 15 minutes.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Temperatures will be very cold tonight but
winds will be relatively light. Therefore wind chills may
fluctuate several degrees rather than remaining consistently
colder than advisory criteria.
properties.instruction:
Use caution while traveling outside. Wear appropriate clothing, a
hat, and gloves.

NWSheadline: WIND CHILL ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 8 PM THIS EVENING TO 8 AM CST FRIDAY
